The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sourav set for a new role at CAB
                                                   Sourav set for a new role at CAB
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Sourav Ganguly is all set to be named chairman of the cricket development committee of the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) at its working committee meeting on Saturday.         
	CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya had said at the annual general meeting, on July 31, that he would like to use the former India captains expertise for the betterment of the game in the state.         
	Sourav will be made the head of the cricket development committee. His suggestions and ideas for the betterment of the game will be sought, said a well-placed source. The source added that the decision was taken in consultation with Sourav.         
	Meanwhile, Bengal started their pre-season fitness camp at the CABs indoor facility on Friday with performance manager Vece Paes focusing on the functional training of the players. Thirty-nine probables, barring pacer Ranadeb Bose, attended the camp. All six ex-Indian Cricket League players were present.         
	A special session is also being planned between the players and Paes, which would deal with creating awareness on anti-doping measures.                                                                                                                       
